Description: iUsem is a social network that posts reviews of what people you know use and recommend.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Minneapolis-Saint Paul Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: iUsem is a social network designed around sharing what you use with real people you know. The idea the company is founded on is that most people would rather get reviews and suggestions from their friends and neighbors rather than random people online.   This is known as word-of-mouth referrals, and has taken place almost exclusively offline.  iUsem seeks to make it easy to connect with a broader range of your friends online to make this word-of-mouth sharing far more useful and prominent than was possible before. Sharing on iUsem takes place through commenting on the various businesses and things you use.  All of your friends' comments show up in a searchable feed.  You can click on any business name to see what everyone says about that business, not just your friends.  You can click on any of your friends to see everything that friend uses. If you are looking for suggestions on what to use, you can ask your friends a question.  Your friends can then respond with what they use and recommend to you. iUsem let's you connect with "Facebook Connect" to bring all of your friend connections with you.  Also, join iUsem groups (businesses, churches, schools, organizations, etc) to connect more easily with the people you know.

Full Description: Empirical Synergies is a Market Research firm servicing the sports & entertainment industry.  Formed to address the growing presence of big data and analytics in the high-stakes decision making process - we offer a suite of web based analytical tools to improve efficiency and accuracy.  A Decade In The Making  Following the 2003 closing of sports powerhouse Woolf Associates, our leadership formed Sports Identity, Inc. with the vision of building a traditional sports marketing firm that would pave the way for the emergence of BrandMatch Score.  In 2011, Empirical Synergies emerged and our premium offering, BrandMatch Score was launched in late 2012.  BrandMatch Score is a ground-breaking Market Research Tool that rates the compatibility between Brands & Endorsers.  Created to provide real-time analytical support and due diligence, brands are no longer forced to make subjective decisions based on syndicated, static data that has no direct correlation to their key attributes or objectives. With the philosophy that "Moneyball" can be applied to marketing, we're disrupting an industry and forcing marketers to change the way they hire endorsers. The software-based product conducts fully customized studies using Real-Time Consumer Insight & Career Performance data to quantify how well a celebrity matches a brand and campaign vision. BrandMatch Score removes subjectivity and mitigates the risk associated with hiring an endorser to represent a brand.  BrandMatch Score finally brings science to the art of identifying endorsers. There is now an objective tool to comprehensively measure compatibility and value.

The Anta Systems team, which consists of experts from the voice communications, data networking and network security industries, has developed an innovative end-to-end Session Initiation Protocol (SIP)-based VoIP solution that includes a fully integrated VoIP Service Switch, a Plug & Play IP-PBX, business-class SIP phones and enhanced applications like IP-Centrex, Visual Voicemail and VoIP Conferencing. Full Description: Look, man has accomplished many things in his journey towards greatness. The skyscraper, the Internet, the automobile, Tiger Woods, and the reverse cowgirl are only a few of his biggest successes. Well, today we can add one more to the list: FourPlay Football, the next evolution of friend leagues. Just like you, we were the first fantasy commissioners before your creepy neighbor and weird co-worker even knew about it.  A decade later we woke up and realized that we love the actual game of football and not just a few all-stars on each team. We like to feel the swings of the game, and we believe that 4th quarters are about rooting for a TEAM. To us, Fantasy Football has become a necessary evil, a fantastic social event which unfortunately consumes too much of our valuable time. We’ve all been there, spending countless hours to “research” how many receptions Kansas City allows to TEs on the road.  Sometimes, despite our efforts, we are obliterated by an untimely turf toe, unforeseen DUI, or Tom Brady’s left knee…in the first game of the season…when we drafted him with the #1 overall pick…F*#kkk! FourPlay Football is a game where YOU control your own destiny. Maybe that’s why we are hearing whispers from our underground users (almost blasphemously) stating, “I like it better than Fantasy.” Cheers, Team FourPlay
